ABUJA – The People’s Redemption Party (PRP) has called on Nigerians to be involved in the Nigeria project and make their voices count, and actions matter in the New Year. The Interim National Chairman of the party, Comrade Adulmajid Yakubu Daudu disclosed this in a statement  to usher in 2022 on Saturday in Abuja Adulmajid expressed hope that 2022 would mark the beginning of a new life for Nigerians: from shackles of inflation, insecurity, and COVID -19 pandemic. PRP Accuses Bauchi Govt Of  Violating National Minimum Wage Act Over 3,000 APC, PRP, NNPP Members Decamp To PDP In Bauchi According to the statement, “Our resolve in this new year must be to stand up and be counted as free citizens in a free country who can decide their own destiny. ” Let’s make our voices count, and our actions matter in our communities and across the country in our push for a better life. And let’s make 2022 our year of redemption. We salute the resilience of Nigerians, and say to our beloved people: Happy New Year!”